                    <p>It was a nice summer afternoon in the suburbs of Bombay when I was born. My parents decided to name me Albert Cosme Monteiro. The name Albert was just a name that my dad liked a lot and so it stuck. Little did he know that March 14th was the birthday of the great Star Albert Einstein. So yes, the star I was referring to is the great Albert Einsteing. So Einstein and I share the same birthday. But that's not where the coincidence ends; believe it or not, we also share the same birth tiem.</p>
