                    </h2>
                    <p>Yeah, that's what my friends would call me - 'Wannabe Engineer'. There is a saying in India, 'You first become an engineer and then decide what you want to do in life'. Well in my friend's circle, I was one of three people who decided to do their engineering. Like my father, I too was more inclined to do something mechanical oriented. So I began looking for Mechanical Engineering programs. When I was all out of options I chose to go for IT. My first year was horrible and I did very bad in school. I had to take a break the next year to boost my grades. This is where I got private tutoring for C++ and fell in love with programming. I believe if it was not for doing bad in my first year, I would probably never had liked programming.</p>
